{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      ProseMirror (via TipTap)\n      Rich document model — thinks in nodes and marks, not raw text\n      \n        \n          Pros\n          \n            TipTap gives you slash commands, drag handles, block types out of the box\n            Native block model — block IDs, block references, drag-and-drop reordering are natural\n            Notion, Linear, and many block editors use this exact stack\n            Collaborative editing ready (Y.js integration is first-class)\n            Richer extension ecosystem for callouts, tables, embeds\n          \n        \n        \n          Cons\n          \n            Document model is JSON, not raw Markdown — need serialization layer to stay markdown-on-disk\n            Markdown round-trip requires careful mapping (especially for custom nodes)\n            Heavier than CodeMirror for simple text editing","choice":"prosemirror","id":null,"timestamp":1775215477648}
